d'', pp. 312\u2013334</ref>\n\n<ref name=curtin-supp1893-baranoir>\"Baranoir, son of a King in Erin, and the Daughter of King under the Wave\" in: {{citation|editor-last=\u00d3 Duilearga |editor-first=S\u00e9amus |editor-link=S\u00e9amus \u00d3 Duilearga |title=Irish Folk-Tales: collected by Jeremiah Curtin (1835-1906) |journal=B\u00e9aloideas |volume=12 |number=1/2 |date=<!--June - -->December 1942 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ccC5yB4BXeoC&q=%22Baranoir%22 |pages=50\u201358 and notes, p. 160<!--ii\u2013v, vii, ix\u2013xvi, 1\u2013166--> |jstor=20522051}}. Originally published by Curtin, ''The Sun'', 28 May 1893.</ref>\n\n<ref name=dasent>{{cite book|ref=harv|editor-last=Dasent |editor-first=G. W., tr. |editorlink=George Webbe Dasent |others=Asbj\u00f8rnsen and Moe (orig. edd.) |title=Popular Tales from the Norse |edition=2nd, enlarged |location=Edinburgh |publisher=Edmonston and Douglas |year=1859 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RZ5JAAAAMAAJ&pg=PR153 |page=cliii}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=dolan-dict>{{cite book|ref=harv |editor-last=Dolan |editor-first=Terence Patrick |editor-link=<!--Terence Patrick Dolan--> |title=leada\u00ed na luatha |work=A Dictionary of Hiberno-English: The Irish Use of English |edition=Rev. |publisher=[[University of Chicago Press]] |origyear= |year=2006 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RN0p1uienWMC&pg=PA138 |page=138 |isbn=0-717-14039-3}}<!--9780717140398--></ref>\n\n<ref name=dorson>{{cite book|ref=harv |editor-last=Dorson |editor-first=Richard M. |editor-link=Richard M. Dorson |title=Le Sabre de la vertu de sagesse |trans-title=The Sword of Wisdom |work=Folktales Told Around the World |publisher=[[University of Chicago Press]] |origyear=1975 |year=2016 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LCVCDgAAQBAJ&pg=PA455 |pages=455\u2013462, 578 |isbn=0-226-37534-X}}<!--9780226375342--></ref>\n\n<ref name=duncan1894>{{citation|last=Duncan |first=Leland L. |authorlink=Leland L. Duncan |title=Review of The Gaelic Journal Vol. IV |jo