5-10-08}} {{s|More_Celtic_Fairy_Tales}}\n* {{citation|editor-last=Kennedy |editor-first=Patrick |authorlink=Patrick Kennedy (folklorist) |title=Legendary Fictions of the Irish Celts |year=1866 |location=London |publisher=Macmillan and Co. |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jfdLAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA255}}\n* {{citation|last=Larminie |first=William |author-link=William Larminie |title=West Irish Folk-Tales and Romances |year=1893 |location=London |publisher=Elliot Stock |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oq9PAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA10}}; [https://archive.org/details/westirishfolktal00larmuoft text] via Internet Archive\n\n;Critical studies\n\n* {{citation|last1=Milne |first1=F. A. |authorlink1=<!--F. A. Milne--> |last2=Nutt |first2=A. Nutt |authorlink2=Alfred Nutt |title=Arthur and Gorlagon |journal=Folklore |volume=15 |number=Folklore |date=25 March 1904 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EpmMyogWOdUC&pg=PA40 |pages=40\u201367 |jstor=1254552}}\n\n* {{Citation|last=Baudi\u0161 |first=Josef |author-link=<!--Josef Baudi\u0161--> |title=On Tochmarc Emere  |journal=\u00c9riu |volume=9 |year=1921\u20131923 |origyear= |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_2HwAAAAMAAJ&q=%22sword+of+light%22 |pages=98\u2013108|jstor=30007915}}\n* {{Citation|last=Briggs |first=Katharine Mary |author-link=Katharine Mary Briggs |chapter=Separable Soul, or external soul |title=An Encyclopedia of Fairies: Hobgoblins, Brownies, Bogies, and Other Supernatural Creaturest |publisher=Pantheon Books |year=1976 |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=da3WAAAAMAAJ&dq=%22sword+of+light%22  |pages=356\u2013357 |isbn=978-0-394-73467-5}}\n* {{citation|last=Bruford |first=Alan |authorlink=Alan Bruford |title=Gaelic Folk-Tales and Medi\u00e6val Romances: A Study of the Early Modern Irish 'Romantic Tales' and Their Oral Derivatives |journal=B\u00e9aloideas |volume=<!--Iml. -->34 |year=1966 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9xTaAAAAMAAJ&q=%22sword%22 |pages=i\u2013v, 1\u2013165, 167\u2013285 |jstor=205213