call-new-song.1986034.html|title=KSI Teams Up With Trippie Redd On New Track \"Wake Up Call\"|website=HotNewHipHop|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> It was released on 31 January 2020 through [[RBC Records]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://respect-mag.com/2020/02/ksi-releases-new-single-and-epic-visual-for-wake-up-call-featuring-trippie-redd/|title=KSI Releases New Single And Epic Visual For \"Wake Up Call\" Featuring Trippie Redd|date=2020-02-01|website=RESPECT.|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> It is the second single from KSI's upcoming 2020 debut album. The song charted at number 11 on the [[UK Singles Chart]], making it KSI's second highest charting single in the UK to date.<ref name=\"OCC\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-weeknd-lands-his-first-uk-number-1-single-with-blinding-lights__28621/|title=The Weeknd scores his first UK Number 1 single|website=www.officialcharts.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/48106/ksi/|title=KSI {{!}} full Official Chart History {{!}} Official Charts Company|website=www.officialcharts.com|access-date=2020-01-27}}</ref>\n\n==Promotion==\nOn 14 January 2020, KSI exclusively revealed during an interview with [[Vice Media|Vice]] that he would be releasing a new song which will \"feature a huge name in American rap\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_uk/article/g5xg94/ksi-logan-paul-youtube-interview|title=Now He's Conquered Logan Paul, KSI Is Ready to Break America|last=Zadeh|first=Jake Lewis,Joe|date=2020-01-14|website=Vice|language=en|access-date=2020-01-25}}</ref> On 25 January, KSI posted the song's artwork to his social media pages, revealing the song's title as \"Wake Up Call\" and the featured artist as Trippie Redd.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/KSIOlajidebt/status/1220860292139225092|title=https://k-s-i.lnk.to/WakeUpCallIS\u00a0pic.twitter.com/zq8KSF3neg|last=KSI|date=2020-01-24|website=@KSIOlajidebt|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> The song was made available for [[pre-order]] on the same day.\n\nShortly after the song was released, KSI started a viral [[TikTok]] video challenge called \"#WakeUpCallChallenge\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://musically.com/2020/02/07/social-star-ksi-debuts-on-tiktok-with-wakeupcallchallenge/|title=Social star KSI debuts on TikTok with #WakeUpCallChallenge|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> TikTok videos using the hashtag have accumulated over 114 million views as of April 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tiktok.com/wakeupcallchallenge?isName=true|title=#wakeupcallchallenge on TikTok|website=TikTok|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\n=== Live performance ===\nOn 13 March 2020, KSI performed the song live during [[BBC]]'s [[Sport Relief|Sport Relief 2020]], which was his first ever televised live music performance.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://metro.co.uk/2020/03/05/ksi-hoping-nail-live-tv-debut-can-hit-mainstream-jokes-messes-meme-worthy-12356896/|title=KSI is hoping to 'nail' live TV debut so he can hit the mainstream|date=2020-03-05|work=Metro|access-date=2020-03-26|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\nThe song entered the UK Singles Chart at number 11, making it KSI's third UK top 40 single and his second highest charting single in the UK to date.<ref name=\"OCC\" /><ref name=\"KSI CH\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/48106/ksi/|title=KSI {{!}} full Official Chart History|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref> During this week, the song peaked at number 2 on the UK [[ITunes Store|iTunes]] Downloads Chart and was the UK's most streamed song on [[YouTube]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.itunescharts.net/uk/artists/music/ksi/songs/wake-up-call-feat-trippie-redd/|title=iTunesCharts.net: 'Wake Up Call (feat. Trippie Redd)' by Ksi (British Songs iTunes Chart)|website=www.itunescharts.net|access-date=2020-02-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/video-streaming-chart/20200207/7508/|title=Official Video Streaming Chart Top 100 {{!}} Official Charts Company|website=www.officialcharts.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> The song dropped to number 28 and number 38 over the following two weeks, before dropping out of the top 40.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20200214/7501/|title=Official Singles Chart Top 100 {{!}} Official Charts Company|website=www.officialcharts.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/|title=Official Singles Chart Top 100 {{!}} Official Charts Company|website=www.officialcharts.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> The song also charted at number 85 on the [[Billboard charts|Billboard]] [[Canadian Hot 100]] and number 92 on the [[Australian Recording Industry Association|ARIA]] Australia Top 100.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/ksi/chart-history/canadian-hot-100|title=KSI|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.auspop.com.au/2020/2/aria-chart-watch-563/|title=ARIA Chart Watch #563|publisher=auspOp|date=8 February 2020|accessdate=8 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Music video ==\nThe music video, directed by Nayip Ramos, was filmed in [[Hollywood]], [[Los Angeles]] in January 2020 and premiered on KSI's YouTube channel on 31 January.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2020/02/01/ksi-channels-austin-powers-new-music-video-shares-love-anesongib-fight-12161262/|title=KSI channels Austin Powers for new music video as he shares love for AnEsonGib|date=2020-02-01|website=Metro|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> As of April 2020, the music video has 12 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=a2KRXcwOeVM|title=KSI - Wake Up Call (feat. Trippie Redd) [Official Music Video]|last=|first=|date=31 January 2020|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> A [[Making-of|behind-the-scenes video]] of the filming of the music video was uploaded to KSI's YouTube channel on 21 February 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wM9P7HKdNho|title=KSI - Wake Up Call (feat. Trippie Redd) BTS|last=|first=|date=21 February 2020|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Remix ==\nA remix of the song by Yoshi, which replaces KSI's two original verses with a new verse by KSI and two new verses by British grime MC [[P Money]] and British YouTuber and fellow [[Sidemen]] member Tobi Brown, was released on 6 March 2020, five weeks after the release of the original song.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://grmdaily.com/video/ksi-wake-up-call-remix-p-money-tobi-yoshi-trippie-redd|title=KSI & Trippie Redd Call On P Money & Tobi For \"Wake Up Call\" Remix|last=|first=|date=6 March 2020|website=GRM Daily|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> An audio visualiser video for the remix was uploaded to KSI's YouTube channel on the day of the remix's release, and as of April 2020, it has 3 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kKqOxADNdLs|title=KSI - Wake Up Call (feat. Trippie Redd, P Money & Tobi) [Yoshi Remix]|last=|first=|date=6 March 2020|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Digital download<ref name=autogenerated2 />\n| title1 = Wake Up Call\n| note1 = featuring [[Trippie Redd]]\n| length1 = 2:55\n| length6 = \n| length10 = \n| title10 = \n| length9 = \n| title9 = \n| length8 = \n| title8 = \n| length7 = \n| title7 = \n| length5 = \n| title6 = \n| title5 = \n| length4 = \n| title4 = \n| length3 = \n| title3 = \n| length2 = \n| title2 = \n| all_writing = \n| total_length = \n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Digital download<ref name=autogen